Renegade Petroleum, Volta Resources: Canadian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a t t   W a l c o f f
-- 
2011-07-15T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/renegade-petroleum-volta-resources-canadian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Canadian trading.  Detour Gold Corp. (DGC)  : The developer of a gold project
in Ontario said it will sell 12.5 million shares at C$29.75 a
share. The stock fell 1.7 percent to C$30.43 before being
halted.  Renegade Petroleum Ltd. (RPL)  : The oil and gas producer
with operations in Saskatchewan received a “buy” rating in new
coverage from Chris Bolton, an analyst at Fraser MacKenzie Ltd.  Volta Resources Inc. (VTR)  : The gold explorer with
operations in West Africa said it is raising C$40 million ($41.7
million) in an equity private placement.  To contact the reporters responsible for this story:
Matt Walcoff in Toronto at 
